seafood is very popular in kerala and the mangalorean coast of karnataka; and chettinad and hyderabad cuisines use meat heavily, and are a lot more spicier. coffee tends to be the preferred drink to tea in south india. to the west, you will find some great cuisine groups. gujarati cuisine is somewhat similar to rajastani cooking with the heavy use of dairy products, but differs in that it is predominantly vegetarian, and often sweetened with jaggery or sugar. gujaratis make some of the best snack items such as the dhokla and the muthia. mumbai is famous for its chaat, as 